release.notes:
Pressed on 180 gram vinyl. Comes with insert, and a [url=https://www.discogs.com/release/7308799]MP3 download card[/url]. Early pressings including [r=2589819] are bare cardboard inside the sleeve, while latter copies are white inside.

Some copies bought in 2020 included a mobile kit as an additional special gift (not packaged inside shrink wrap) to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the release.

©&℗ 2000/2010 Third Man Records LCC, 623 7th Avenue South Nashville, TN 37203 

Recorded at Third Man Studio, SW Detroit at the turn of the century.
"Death Letter" published by Sondick Music, "Your Southern Can Is Mine" published by Columbia Phonograph Co.
This album is dedicated to Blind Willie McTell and Gerrit Rietveld.
